{# ── DISCLOSURE BANNER · ABOVE THE FOLD (Sheet-7 rule 1). Canonical .disclosure class
     (03-conversion.css) reused here. The inBrief above already states the NOT-Intuit boundary
     directly under the dark hero; this banner makes it unmissable a SECOND time and renders
     the explicit intent split (Intuit-account vs. your-books) as a checks-list with the Intuit
     support link. This is the most reputation-sensitive page on the site — honesty is the
     whole point. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="qb-support-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure disclosure--warn">
      <svg class="disclosure__icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#A4660A" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 11v5M12 7.5v.3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      <div class="disclosure__body"><strong>TechBrot is an independent accounting firm of Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors. We are not Intuit.</strong> For account, billing, or subscription issues, contact Intuit directly <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">&rarr;</a> &mdash; we cannot access your Intuit account, change your subscription, reset your login, or fix the QuickBooks software. This page is an independent firm&rsquo;s guide to reaching the right help; it is not Intuit&rsquo;s official QuickBooks support.</div>
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list" id="qb-support-boundaries">
      <li><strong>Contact Intuit for the account itself:</strong> Intuit login, password, or two-factor; subscription, renewal, refund, or billing; and QuickBooks software bugs, outages, or Intuit-side error codes. <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Go to Intuit support <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a> &mdash; only Intuit can access your account.</li>
      <li><strong>Talk to an independent ProAdvisor for your own books:</strong> a broken company file, errors inside the file, a cleanup, a setup or migration, payroll-in-file, and CPA-ready books &mdash; the accounting work, fixed-fee.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SHORT VERSION · TL;DR prose — the honest meta-answer in one paragraph. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="qb-support-tldr">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Which &ldquo;support&rdquo; do you actually need?</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose" id="qb-support-tldr-body">{{ tldr | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. First question is the honesty question. ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Contacting QuickBooks support, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="qb-support-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INTUIT'S REAL CHANNELS · grid-3 buyer-cards, one per product. HONESTY HARD LIMIT:
     channels are described GENERICALLY — NO phone number, NO hours, NO wait times, NO "24/7"
     anywhere; each card defers current specifics to Intuit's official support link. ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-channels">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Intuit&rsquo;s real support channels</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How to reach Intuit, by product.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">These are the channels Intuit actually operates &mdash; in-product Help and the virtual assistant, the official QuickBooks support site and Community forums, and a contact/callback request flow. Desktop, Payroll, and Payments each have their own paths. <strong>We don&rsquo;t publish Intuit phone numbers, hours, or wait times here</strong> &mdash; those change, and fabricating them would be dishonest. For current specifics, go straight to <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit&rsquo;s official support</a>.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in channels %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ c.product | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body"><strong>Channels:</strong> {{ c.what | safe }}</p>
        <p class="buyer-card__body"><strong>Can help with:</strong> {{ c.can | safe }}</p>
        <p class="buyer-card__body"><strong>Can&rsquo;t help with:</strong> {{ c.cant | safe }}</p>
        <p class="buyer-card__body"><strong>How to escalate:</strong> {{ c.escalate | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── TRIAGE · the load-bearing honest split (Sheet-7 rule 6). grid-2 of two checks-lists:
     Contact Intuit for… vs. Talk to an independent ProAdvisor for… ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-triage">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Where your issue belongs</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Intuit, or an independent ProAdvisor?</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The fastest way to the right help is to know which bucket your problem falls in. Anything touching your Intuit account goes to Intuit; anything inside your books comes to an independent firm.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Contact Intuit for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for t in triageIntuit %}
          <li>{{ t | safe }}</li>
          {%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Go to Intuit support <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Talk to an independent ProAdvisor for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for t in triageProAdvisor %}
          <li>{{ t | safe }}</li>
          {%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">Get the free file review <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── THE INDEPENDENT PATH · grid-3 buyer-cards — the three honest reasons to bring it to a firm. ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-independent">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The independent path</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">When it&rsquo;s the books, not the software.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">No software support line can fix accounting that&rsquo;s wrong inside your file. That&rsquo;s what an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm does &mdash; on a fixed fee, scoped in writing.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for p in independentPath %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ p.signal | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ p.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="buyer-card__body"><strong>Honest scope:</strong> {{ p.honest | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PHONE CTA · call-breakout. Phone label is ALWAYS "Talk to a Certified ProAdvisor
     (independent firm)" (Sheet-7 rule 4) — never "QuickBooks support line". ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-call">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="call-breakout">
      <div>
        <p class="call-breakout__title">Need help with the accounting inside your file?</p>
        <p class="call-breakout__sub">A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor at TechBrot reviews your situation &mdash; a broken file, a cleanup, a setup or migration, payroll-in-file. The file review and discovery call are free; a written fixed-fee scope follows within 3 business days. {{ site.phone.display }} &middot; independent firm, not Intuit. For an Intuit account, billing, or login issue, <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">contact Intuit directly</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="tel:{{ site.phone.e164 }}" data-tb-event="phone_click">Talk to a Certified ProAdvisor (independent firm)</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 8 contract Q/A as faq__list; visible list = FAQPage schema (same array). FIRST
     question MUST be "Is this Intuit's official QuickBooks support?" answered No (Sheet-7
     rule 2). ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask about QuickBooks support.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qb-support-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="qb-support-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PAGE REVIEW · firm-level (founder-name-zero). David survives only as reviewedBy @id in
     schema. ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Honest-routing standards.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This guide is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot</strong>, an independent ProAdvisor firm. We deliberately describe Intuit&rsquo;s support channels generically and do not publish Intuit phone numbers, hours, wait times, or &ldquo;24/7&rdquo; claims &mdash; those change, and stating them would mislead; for current specifics we link to <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit&rsquo;s official support</a>. TechBrot is an independent firm &mdash; not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by <a href="https://www.intuit.com/" rel="noopener nofollow">Intuit Inc.</a>; it provides no Intuit account, billing, subscription, login, or QuickBooks product support, and does not file tax returns or represent clients before the IRS. QuickBooks and Intuit are registered trademarks of Intuit Inc.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-18</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-18</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-18 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · grid-2 buyer-cards. The Intuit support card is the canonical redirect for
     account/billing/login/subscription intent (Sheet-7 rule 6). ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-related">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where to go next.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading"><a href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ r.title | safe }}</a></h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ r.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
